[[File:Reward casket (elite) detail.png|left|130px]]
A '''[[reward casket]] (elite)''' is received after from completing the final clue of an [[Clue scroll (elite)|elite clue scroll]] trail, and contains the reward for the trail.

While players can only have one of each type of clue scroll in their possession, they can possess unlimited amounts of reward caskets, and are eligible to receive clue scrolls again once it is obtained.

==Rewards==
Elite clues generate a minimum of 4 rewards and a maximum of 6, granting an average of 5 rewards per casket. The rewards consist of generic items, shared treasure trail items, and items that are unique for elite clues. Additionally, players have a 1/5 chance to receive a [[master clue scroll]] upon opening an elite casket.

There is also a 1/35 chance of the reward casket being a [[mimic]], which can be taken to the [[strange casket]] in [[Watson]]'s house to fight [[The Mimic]]. Players are only eligible to receive mimics if they have spoken to the strange casket to enable the chance of a reward casket turning into a mimic. If a player attempts to open an elite reward casket for the first time before speaking to the strange casket, they will be asked whether they want a chance of a Mimic boss fight or not, and wanting it will result in the chatbox directing players to the strange casket.

All droprates (except for the [[Mimic]] rewards) are confirmed by Mod Tide.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Tide|url=https://twitter.com/JagexTide/status/1131933683714330624|date=24 May 2019|archiveurl=https://archive.fo/WUqwD|archivedate=24 May 2019|quote=I know its been a while since the clue expansion but here is the information on clue scroll drop rates and loot chances! If anything changes I will keep you posted.|name=Clue rates tweet}}{{CiteGeneral|url=https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/16pVNHdZyynmxIbM9mynRDYT0LQsWxq-vbDs4_7DpnGM/edit?usp=sharing|title=Clue scrolls 2019|author=|time=24 May 2019}} The listed rarities are per roll.

The average loot roll is worth {{Coins|floor({{EliteClueValue}})}}. On average, elite clues are worth {{Coins|floor(5 * {{EliteClueValue}})}}. The 1/5 chance of receiving a master clue scroll adds another {{Coins|floor(1/5 * 6 * {{MasterClueValue}})}}, for a total expected value per clue of {{Coins|floor(5 * {{EliteClueValue}} + 1/5 * 6 * {{MasterClueValue}})}}.

